	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p>per Steamer via <placeName>Halifax</placeName></p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St Thomas</placeName> <date>18th Jany 1864</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
				<p>Revd. Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I take leave to address you the<lb/> present to request if you will kindly oblige me to<lb/> have printed for me&#44; in Hebrew&#44; twenty five copies<lb/> of the seven verses of the Akafot read at burials&#59;<lb/> affixed&#44; should it not cost more than 25 cents each<lb/> or &#36;6.25&#47;00 for the 25 copies.  The size of each copy<lb/> must be exactly that of the <sic>inclosed</sic> slip of paper<lb/> consequently it will admit a good size type as I would<lb/> desire the entire size of the paper to be made use of<lb/> leaving no blank space below&#44; except the margin &#38; the<lb/> space required between each verse.  Please let the<lb/> quality of the paper be as good &#38; stout as the enclosed<lb/> piece&#44; or better if possible.  Please when sending the<lb/> same not to fold the paper as they are intended<lb/> to be pasted on boards to read by at the Bet Haim&#44;<lb/> but put them up in a roll securely tied &#38; sealed &#38;<lb/> put the parcel in the ship&#39;s letter bag should there<lb/> be one direct or via <placeName>New York</placeName>&#44; addressing the<lb/> said parcel to me &#38; writing on it &#8220;papers&#8221;.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The amount of this small commission I<lb/> will immediately on receipt of your advice pay over<lb/> to any party here you may desire.  I trust you</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>will excuse the trouble this small commission will<lb/> occasion you&#44; it being for a religious purpose &#38;<lb/> required for the congregation&#44; of which I am at present the<lb/> vice president whose <del>duty</del> office is to look after these<lb/> matters connected with funerals.  Relying that<lb/> you will forward this small commission as early<lb/> as possible &#38; awaiting your reply.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I remain Revd Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">With sentiments of the highest respect</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Your Most obdt Servant</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><hi rend="underline"><persName role="author">B Delvalle</persName></hi></p>
				<p>P. S. Should you have any parcel sending to any party here<lb/> you may if you please&#44; include the above.</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>per Steamer via <placeName>Halifax</placeName></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
		</body>
